@dev The function allows users to filled orders and make trades.
 Requirements:
 - the order must exist and `id_` of order cannot be higher than `_orderCount`.
 - order cannot be filled already.
 - order cannot be cancelled already.
 @param id_ id of the order to be filled.
 Emits a {OrderFilled} event.

Deposit(address,address,uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when the user deposits the tokens to the exchange.

params.balance: the exchange balance of these user tokens after deposit.
params.user: address of the user that deposited tokens.

OrderCancelled(uint256,address,address,u.details: Emitted when the user cancel an order.

params.amountGet: the amount of `tokenGet` token user wanted to get previously.
params.amountGive: the amount of `tokenGive` token user wanted to give previously.
params.tokenGet: the address of the token that the user wanted to get previously.
params.tokenGive: the address of the token that the user wanted to give previously.
params.user: address of the user that cancelled this order.

OrderCreated(uint256,address,address,uin.details: Emitted when the user create an order.

params.amountGet: the amount of `tokenGet` token user wants to get.
params.amountGive: the amount of `tokenGive` token user wants to give.
params.tokenGet: the address of the token that the user wants to get.
params.tokenGive: the address of the token that the user wants to give.
params.user: address of the user that create this order.

params.amountGet: the amount of `tokenGet` token user received.
params.amountGive: the amount of `tokenGive` token user gived.
params.tokenGet: the address of the token that user received.
params.tokenGive: the address of the token that the user gived.
params.user: address of the user that create this order.
params.userFill: address of the user that maked this deal with `user`.

Withdraw(address,address,uint256,uint256.details: Emitted when the user withdraws the tokens from the exchange.

params.balance: the exchange balance of these user tokens after withdrawn.
params.token: the address of the token to be withdrawn.
params.user: address of the user to whom funds are withdrawn.

balanceOf(address,address).details: Returns the balance of an individual token of an individual user.

params.token_: address of token or Ether internal address to be explored.
params.user_: user's address to check the amount of `token_` they has on the exchange.

cancelOrder(uint256).details: The function allows users to cancel and remove their own orders from orderbook. Requirements: - `msg.sender` must be the creator of `id_` order. - the order must exist.

params.id_: id of the order to be removed from orderbook. Emits a {OrderCancelled} event.

params.feeAccount_: the address to which all fees will be transferred.
params.feePercent_: percentage of fees from each transaction to be charged.

depositEther().details: The function allows users to deposit Ether to exchange. Requirements: - `msg.value` cannot be zero. Emits a {Deposit} event.

depositToken(address,uint256).details: The function allows users to deposit erc-20 tokens to exchange. Requirements: - `token_` address cannot be `ETHER` ( or address(0) ) address. - `msg.sender` required to approve amount of `token_` to be deposited to this contract.

params.amount_: the amount of `token_` to be deposited. Emits a {Deposit} event.
params.token_: address of the token to be deposited.

fillOrder(uint256).details: The function allows users to filled orders and make trades. Requirements: - the order must exist and `id_` of order cannot be higher than `_orderCount`. - order cannot be filled already. - order cannot be cancelled already.

params.id_: id of the order to be filled. Emits a {OrderFilled} event.

getFeeAccount().details: Returns the address of the fee account that receives exchange fees.

getFeePercent().details: Returns the fee percent of every transaction.

getOrder(uint256).details: Returns the Order data by providing order Id.

getOrderCancelled(uint256).details: Returns by providing order Id the bool whether the order was cancelled.

getOrderCount().details: Returns the amount of all orders.

getOrderFilled(uint256).details: Returns by providing order Id the bool whether the order was filled.

makeOrder(address,uint256,address,uint25.details: The function allows users to create and add orders to orderbook. Requirements: - `amountGet_` cannot be zero. - `amountGive_` cannot be zero.

params.amountGet_: the amount of `tokenGet` token user wants to get.
params.amountGive_: the amount of `tokenGive` token user wants to give. Emits a {OrderCreated} event.
params.tokenGet_: the address of the token that the user wants to get.
params.tokenGive_: the address of the token that the user wants to give.

withdrawEther(uint256).details: The function allows users to withdraw Ether from exchange. Requirements: - `amount_` cannot be zero. - user must have enough `amount_` of `ETHER` in `_tokens` mapping.

params.amount_: the amount of ETH to be withdrawn. Emits a {Withdraw} event.

withdrawToken(address,uint256).details: The function allows users to withdraw erc-20 tokens from exchange. Requirements: - `token_` address cannot be `ETHER` ( or address(0) ) address. - user must have enough `amount_` of `token_` in `_tokens` mapping.

params.amount_: the amount of `token_` to be withdrawn. Emits a {Withdraw} event.
